Detects circular module dependencies within a crate by running `cargo modules`; catches cycles that Cargo's own checker misses (Cargo rejects circular *crate* deps but allows circular *module* deps, which the spec forbids).

The script is a stub: it only verifies that `cargo modules dependencies --no-externs --no-sysroot --no-uses` runs without error. Actual cycle detection via DOT graph parsing is deferred to a dylint rule (see docs/DYLINT_RULES.md). The `--no-externs --no-sysroot --no-uses` flags narrow output to module-level dependencies, though flag support varies across cargo-modules versions.

Requires `cargo-modules` installed; exits with code 1 if the tool is missing or the command fails, 0 on success.